<sect1 id="columns">
<title
>Columns</title>

<para
>You can divide the page into several columns, of equal width, with
a user controlled space in between each column.</para>

<note>
<para
>This feature is only available in Word processing Templates.</para>

<para
>If you are working in a <acronym
>DTP</acronym
> Template, you can
build up several columns using a different frame for each column.</para>
</note>

<para
>To change the number and width of columns:</para>

<procedure>
<step>
<para
>First, you must be in Frame Edit Mode.  If you are not currently
in frame edit mode, you can change to Frame Edit Mode, in one of three
ways:</para>

<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para
>Select <menuchoice
> <guimenu
>Tools</guimenu
><guimenuitem
>Edit
Frames</guimenuitem
></menuchoice
> from the Menu bar</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para
>You can use the keyboard shortcut:
<keycombo
><keycap
>F5</keycap
></keycombo
></para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para
>or by clicking <inlinemediaobject
><imageobject
><imagedata
fileref="framemode.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject
></inlinemediaobject
> on
the tool-bar.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</step>

<step>
<para
>Place the mouse cursor inside the frame you want to move, and
click once with the <mousebutton
>left</mousebutton
> mouse button. This
selects this frame as the current frame.</para>
</step>

<step>
<para
>Select <menuchoice>
<guimenu
>Format</guimenu
><guimenuitem
>Page</guimenuitem
></menuchoice>
from the Menu bar.</para>

<para
>This will bring up a dialog box</para>

<screenshot>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="wpfmtpg1.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</step>
<step>
<para
>Click on the table labeled <guilabel
>Columns</guilabel
>.</para>

<para
>This will change the dialog panel.</para>

<screenshot>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject
><imagedata fileref="wpfmtpg2.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</step>

<step>
<para
>You can now select the number of columns, and the spacing in
between.</para>

<para
>The preview box shows you what you can expect.</para>
</step>

<step>
<para
>Click <guibutton
>OK</guibutton
> when you are done.</para>
</step>

<step>
<para
>Click <guibutton
>Cancel</guibutton
> to abort changes.</para>
</step>
</procedure>
</sect1>

